Ah, I'm a bit of a python newbie but this is quite easy using [External Pipelines](https://docs.dagster.io/guides/build/external-pipelines)

Instead of relying on `shutil` to find the python executable, ensure that a proper venv has been created for the secondary project. Then, call this python instead:
```python

import dagster as dg


@dg.asset
def wrapper_asset(
    context: dg.AssetExecutionContext, pipes_subprocess_client: dg.PipesSubprocessClient
) -> None:
    external_python_code_dir = "/opt/my-project"

    return pipes_subprocess_client.run(
        command=[f'{external_python_code_dir}/.venv/bin/python', f'{external_python_code_dir}/external_code.py'],
        context=context,
    ).get_results()


@dg.definitions
def resources():
    return dg.Definitions(
        resources={"pipes_subprocess_client": dg.PipesSubprocessClient()}
    )

```

