Run status sensors currently don’t support yielding RunRequest. So, I'd recommend to write a custom [sensor](https://docs.dagster.io/concepts/partitions-schedules-sensors/sensors#defining-a-sensor) that listens to the run storage and yields a RunRequest when a `job_1` run finishes.

Something like:
```python
from dagster import RunsFilter, sensor, DagsterRunStatus

@sensor(job=do_the_second_thing)
def thing_sensor(context):
    run_records = context.instance.get_run_records(
        filters=RunsFilter(
            job_name="do_the_first_thing",
            statuses=[DagsterRunStatus.SUCCESS],
            updated_after=..., # can also filter by timestamp to do more efficient fetching
        ),
        order_by="update_timestamp",
        ascending=False,
    )
    for run_record in run_records:
        yield RunRequest(
            run_key=run_record.dagster_run.run_id,  # avoid double firing for the same run
        )
```

